{"author":{"id":"69a73b59e8bca0653e9174a374f9f55c998c9a49750b37bad6bd3960e96b7ca3"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1719511634,"nonce":"B0/uiaXxlg6GdRhgPjJpDRWfySI=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDODBZtRc6C2osg","github-url":"https://github.com/dandi/dandi-cli/issues/1455#issuecomment-2195360544"},"message":"@rcpeene The `download()` function uses its own client instance, so doing `client = dandiapi.DandiAPIClient(token=dandi_api_key)` has no effect on it.  As @waxlamp said, setting the API key via an environment variable may be the simplest way to pass it to `download()`.\n\nIt seems you previously stored your API key in an encrypted keyring file on the system.  You can remove this keyfile and start over by deleting `~/.local/share/python_keyring/crypted_pass.cfg`.  See [the handbook](https://www.dandiarchive.org/handbook/13_upload/#storing-access-credentials) for more information on how dandi uses keyrings.","files":null}]}